column5: Hi Guys, Looking for a spot to go Walleye fishing in late September or early October. In hopes of catching some nice Walleye. Anybody that could give me some ideas would be greatly appreciatted...Thanks in advance,Doug

I have been going to Northwest Ontario in late September for the last 10 years ! Just a suggestion, the outfitters that offer Moose hunts normally stay open later for fishing! This year we are going out of Slate Falls Outpost in Sioux Lookout! Flying to Lake St. Joe for 7 days! Verne Hollett is the owner ! Nice fish but normally have to go deeper! Weather can be 75 and it can be 25 !!!!!! Good Luck!!!!!
Traverse Bay - Winnipeg River (world class Walleye - put this spot up against anything out there).
